    "type": "VerificationActivity",
    "name": "Systematic Grid Convergence Study for CFD Blood Pump Model",
    "description": "A structured grid convergence investigation was conducted across three mesh refinement levels (coarse: 2.1M cells, medium: 6.4M cells, fine: 18.7M cells) for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry. The Richardson extrapolation procedure per ASME V&V 20 was applied to quantify the grid convergence index (GCI) for the primary quantity of interest (volume-averaged shear stress). Target GCI threshold was set at 5% for the medium-to-fine refinement ratio.",
    "activityType": "GridConvergenceVerification",
    "performedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/org/morrison-lab",
